prison for ten years.

03:40.288 --> 03:42.155
I'm supposed to sit
in there and fucking rot

03:42.290 --> 03:43.824
while you go and do
your fucking case?

03:43.891 --> 03:45.593
That's the only thing
you care about!

03:45.659 --> 03:47.219
You don't give a shit
about anyone else!

03:47.295 --> 03:48.805
People have been killed.
Do you know that?

03:48.829 --> 03:50.989
I know that, yeah.
Well, you didn't
save fucking Rachel!

03:51.031 --> 03:52.666
What are you going to do for me?

03:57.471 --> 04:00.040
You're too fucking fancy
for this place!

04:00.107 --> 04:01.775
Get the fuck out of here!

04:05.513 --> 04:07.615
Okay, you sleep well, okay?

04:09.717 --> 04:12.353
I came here to try, all right?

04:19.927 --> 04:21.562
Oh, fuck.

04:33.040 --> 04:35.909
Finally. Are we set?

04:35.976 --> 04:38.712
We just came from a meeting
with the management committee.

04:38.779 --> 04:41.615
There's no way
you can get in that
witness chair, Donald.

04:41.682 --> 04:43.183
I have been summoned.

04:43.250 --> 04:44.452
We can get you out of that.

04:44.518 --> 04:46.219
You are part
of the defense team.

04:46.354 --> 04:47.788
Anything you would say
is shielded

04:47.855 --> 04:48.855
by both privilege

04:48.889 --> 04:49.923
and work product.

04:49.990 --> 04:50.990
That was once true.

04:51.024 --> 04:52.660
It is no longer so.

04:52.726 --> 04:55.563
After Wendell Corey
chose to invoke my name

04:55.629 --> 04:57.197
during his testimony,

04:57.264 --> 04:59.366
legally he waived the privilege

04:59.367 --> 05:02.369
by raising a reliance
on counsel defense.

05:02.370 --> 05:04.705
You know this plays
right into Billy's hands.

05:04.772 --> 05:06.674
He has no case right now.

05:06.740 --> 05:09.276
By you taking the stand,
you risk giving him one.

05:09.377 --> 05:11.379
The fact that his case
rests on me...

05:11.445 --> 05:12.513
what more could we want?

05:12.580 --> 05:13.947
This isn't about you.

05:14.014 --> 05:15.616
It isn't about your ego

05:15.683 --> 05:18.185
or your intelligence
or your Billy grudge.

05:18.251 --> 05:19.553
This is about you

05:19.620 --> 05:21.389
doing what is best
for the client.

05:21.422 --> 05:23.023
Ohh.

05:24.425 --> 05:26.002
And you can't use that
damn thing in court.

05:26.026 --> 05:30.063
Are you saying they might
see me as a monster?

05:30.130 --> 05:31.198
You're damn right.

05:31.264 --> 05:32.933
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, Letts.

05:35.035 --> 05:36.870
I have been summoned.

05:38.105 --> 05:40.407
I will comply
with the court order,

05:40.408 --> 05:43.411
and I will discharge
my civic duty.

05:44.712 --> 05:46.414
Donald.

05:46.447 --> 05:48.416
Did you puppeteer this?

05:49.417 --> 05:50.551
You told Wendell

05:50.618 --> 05:51.885
to hide behind privilege,

05:51.952 --> 05:53.887
knowing full well
that they would ask you

05:53.954 --> 05:55.022
to the stand.

05:56.223 --> 05:58.626
This is the big day.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.728
We don't want to be late.

06:00.794 --> 06:04.432
The risk you are putting us
through is enormous.

06:04.498 --> 06:06.600
I need to get to court.

06:28.956 --> 06:32.993
What a sight you all are for me.

06:34.462 --> 06:37.465
You may find my appearance odd.

06:37.531 --> 06:39.933
Remember, I am in no pain.

07:20.007 --> 07:21.675
You are my people.

07:23.243 --> 07:25.579
I'm your people.

08:01.749 --> 08:03.551
Do you solemnly swear
to tell the truth,

08:03.584 --> 08:04.584
so help you God?

08:04.618 --> 08:06.019
Yes, I do.

08:07.254 --> 08:08.589
I'm sorry. I didn't hear that.

08:12.560 --> 08:15.262
Yes, I do, I said.

08:15.328 --> 08:16.328
Hmm.

08:17.565 --> 08:19.066
Sir, in a nice loud voice,

08:19.132 --> 08:22.035
please introduce yourself
to the members of our jury.

08:23.203 --> 08:25.773
Donald Cooperman.

08:27.374 --> 08:28.909
And you're an attorney.

08:28.976 --> 08:30.043
Yes.

08:30.110 --> 08:31.311
A well-compensated,

08:31.378 --> 08:33.380
Yale-educated attorney.

08:33.446 --> 08:34.948
Not only Yale, but yes.

08:35.015 --> 08:38.284
You represent the defendant,
Borns Technology?

08:38.351 --> 08:39.852
Yes.

08:39.919 --> 08:42.255
As an experienced attorney,
you're familiar

08:42.322 --> 08:44.592
with something called the
advice of counsel defense.

08:44.658 --> 08:47.595
That's a legal doctrine
involving...

08:49.663 --> 08:52.365
good faith reliance

08:52.432 --> 08:56.169
on an attorney's, uh...

08:56.236 --> 08:57.504
advice.

08:57.605 --> 08:59.239
Let me pose a hypothetical.

08:59.306 --> 09:03.944
If someone like Borns Tech
were to detonate napalm bombs

09:04.011 --> 09:05.713
off the coast of Long Beach,

09:05.779 --> 09:07.579
which is just a few miles
from this courtroom,

09:07.615 --> 09:10.483
that defense could come in
pretty handy, couldn't it?

09:10.618 --> 09:12.920
I don't agree with your premise.

09:12.986 --> 09:16.056
A clever attorney
could invoke that defense

09:16.123 --> 09:19.259
to help his client
avoid responsibility.

09:19.326 --> 09:20.393
It's a...

09:20.460 --> 09:21.629
it's... it's... it's...

09:21.695 --> 09:24.965
it's a legitimate
legal defense...

09:25.032 --> 09:27.334
honored in courts
across the land.

09:27.400 --> 09:28.769
Ever advise Borns Tech

09:28.836 --> 09:30.537
about testing cluster bombs
in the ocean?

09:30.638 --> 09:32.940
I did not.

09:33.006 --> 09:35.175
- Wendell Corey says you did.
- That's not what he said

09:35.242 --> 09:37.244
on the closed circuit
television replay I saw,

09:37.310 --> 09:41.214
but if he did say that
in some other venue,

09:41.281 --> 09:42.683
I would say he was mistaken.

09:42.750 --> 09:45.485
Did you advise
or instruct Ryan Larson

09:45.552 --> 09:46.854
or anyone else at Borns Tech

09:46.920 --> 09:48.555
to design or test cluster bombs?

09:48.656 --> 09:50.724
No. I did not.

09:50.791 --> 09:53.694
Did a man named Karl Stoltz
ever authorize Ryan Larson

09:53.761 --> 09:55.896
to test cluster bombs?

09:55.963 --> 09:59.867
Uh, I've never heard of anyone
by the name of Karl Stoltz.

09:59.933 --> 10:02.002
Are you familiar with
the original plaintiff

10:02.069 --> 10:04.171
in this lawsuit...
Rachel Kennedy?

10:04.237 --> 10:05.806
Only from the pleadings.

10:05.873 --> 10:07.607
Hmm. She had to drop
out of the suit

10:07.675 --> 10:09.710
after she was run over
by a car and killed.

10:09.777 --> 10:12.646
Mm, yeah, I... I know...

10:12.713 --> 10:14.581
I know she had to drop out.

10:14.648 --> 10:15.916
Who's Lucy Kittridge?

10:15.983 --> 10:17.685
How is this remotely relevant?

10:17.751 --> 10:19.186
I was just getting to that.

10:19.252 --> 10:21.288
You and Miss Kittridge had
a personal relationship.

10:21.354 --> 10:22.656
Right?

10:22.723 --> 10:24.658
She worked for the firm.

10:24.725 --> 10:26.326
Are you aware of a conversation

10:26.393 --> 10:29.329
between Miss Kittridge
and a man named Karl Stoltz?

10:29.396 --> 10:30.764
Objection. Hearsay.

10:30.831 --> 10:32.599
Not offering
for the truth, Your Honor.

10:32.666 --> 10:34.668
Are you aware of a conversation?

10:34.735 --> 10:38.972
I don't know anyone
named Stoltz.

10:39.039 --> 10:40.140
Very well.

10:40.207 --> 10:42.609
Are you aware Mr. Stoltz
made threats on your life?

10:42.676 --> 10:44.678
Can we at least get
an offer of proof?

10:44.745 --> 10:46.413
- Where is this going?
- My offer of proof

10:46.479 --> 10:49.316
is that Mr. Stoltz made
threats against this witness,

10:49.382 --> 10:51.551
and then the next day
he wound up dead

10:51.618 --> 10:52.953
in the trunk of a car.

10:53.020 --> 10:54.721
What's the basis
of knowledge here?

10:55.823 --> 10:57.490
It was my car.

10:57.557 --> 10:59.927
There isn't a scrap of evidence

10:59.993 --> 11:03.296
tying our client to a murder.

11:03.363 --> 11:04.732
So if Lucy Kittridge...

11:04.765 --> 11:06.967
there she is
right here... Lucy...

11:07.034 --> 11:08.301
if she gets on the stand

11:08.368 --> 11:10.738
and testifies that you
know Karl Stoltz,

11:10.804 --> 11:12.605
- would she be lying?
- Objection.

11:12.740 --> 11:14.174
Calls for speculation.

11:14.241 --> 11:16.910
Well, Miss Kittridge is going
to be my next witness.

11:16.977 --> 11:19.379
I will take it to bene.
Go ahead.

11:19.446 --> 11:21.114
Miss Kittridge is going to say

11:21.181 --> 11:23.951
that Mr. Stoltz
had a conversation
with you.

11:34.527 --> 11:37.030
You know what I find, uh...

11:39.199 --> 11:41.068
unconscionable?

11:41.134 --> 11:42.803
Yes, please.

11:46.573 --> 11:48.208
A bottom-feeding vulture

11:48.275 --> 11:50.143
picking flesh
off the bones of the dead

11:50.210 --> 11:52.312
at the expense
of a great company,

11:52.379 --> 11:57.885
one that employs thousands
of Americans with good jobs,

11:57.951 --> 12:01.221
all the while protecting
American interests

12:01.288 --> 12:03.623
here and abroad.

12:03.690 --> 12:05.325
And making you
and Wendell Corey rich.

12:05.392 --> 12:08.862
We get paid well because
we do our work well.

12:09.863 --> 12:11.698
The beneficiaries of that work

12:11.799 --> 12:14.334
are not just Borns Tech.

12:14.401 --> 12:17.470
It's everyone.

12:17.537 --> 12:19.206
Even you.

12:19.272 --> 12:20.407
Me?

12:20.473 --> 12:22.275
Yeah. You, sir...

12:24.211 --> 12:25.512
I have...

12:27.815 --> 12:31.819
As a soldier, as a lawyer,
as a citizen,

12:31.852 --> 12:35.823
I have given my life
to this country's...

12:35.856 --> 12:38.125
this nation's fundamental
infrastructures,

12:38.191 --> 12:43.096
its systems of law and security.

12:43.163 --> 12:48.435
It's what allows little men
like you your day in court.

12:48.501 --> 12:49.501
It...

12:51.238 --> 12:53.340
Even when it means letting you

12:53.406 --> 12:55.308
try to commit fraud.

12:55.375 --> 12:57.510
Miss Kittridge
will take the stand

12:57.577 --> 13:01.114
and testify that you
damn well know Karl Stoltz.

13:01.181 --> 13:02.849
Is it still your testimony

13:02.850 --> 13:04.952
that you do not know
Karl Stoltz?

13:06.053 --> 13:07.554
I know what he is.

13:09.422 --> 13:11.624
I know what you are.

13:11.691 --> 13:12.860
This is your last chance

13:12.893 --> 13:14.361
to set the record straight, sir.

13:22.870 --> 13:24.037
I know...

13:28.175 --> 13:30.944
Mr. Cooperman, can you finish
answering the question?

13:35.348 --> 13:36.884
Mr. Cooperman.

13:39.686 --> 13:41.721
Can you answer the question?

13:41.788 --> 13:43.891
- Oh!
- Mr. Cooperman!

14:06.479 --> 14:08.115
Are those new glasses?

14:09.549 --> 14:11.618
Yeah.
Cute, right?

14:14.454 --> 14:15.622
- Hey.
- Billy.

14:15.688 --> 14:16.688
How's it going?

14:16.723 --> 14:18.025
So what's up?

14:18.091 --> 14:19.526
How's he doing?

14:19.592 --> 14:20.994
He had a stroke.

14:21.061 --> 14:22.529
There's some bleeding
on the brain.

14:22.595 --> 14:25.565
He's getting an MRI now
to determine how much.

14:27.800 --> 14:29.069
Was he sick or anything?

14:29.136 --> 14:30.803
Did he show any signs of it?

14:30.938 --> 14:32.081
Well, the doctor just told me

14:32.105 --> 14:34.041
that he had some sort
of a mini-stroke

14:34.107 --> 14:35.442
three months ago,

14:35.508 --> 14:37.510
so maybe that's why
he's been acting crazy.

15:22.455 --> 15:24.791
You know his testimony
now, it's not going to...

15:24.857 --> 15:26.159
Yeah, I know.

15:27.227 --> 15:28.628
I didn't get a chance to...

15:28.695 --> 15:29.695
Seriously.

15:32.265 --> 15:35.001
I didn't get a chance
to cross-examine him, so...

15:35.002 --> 15:36.436
No, I get it.

15:49.149 --> 15:51.151
I can't afford to let it go.

15:51.218 --> 15:53.120
I'm not going to let it go.

16:07.567 --> 16:10.603
Is there any question
as to what we should do?

16:10.670 --> 16:12.739
No. We should go forward.

16:12.805 --> 16:14.374
What?

16:14.441 --> 16:16.109
Well, we're winning, Wendell.

16:16.176 --> 16:19.879
They've put on
a thin case at best.

16:19.946 --> 16:21.581
We're in a good position.

16:21.648 --> 16:25.118
Cooperman actually
seemed sympathetic.

16:25.185 --> 16:27.054
Whoever thought
that was possible?

16:28.421 --> 16:29.522
Leonard?

16:31.124 --> 16:32.725
Your call, Wendell.

16:32.792 --> 16:35.062
M... Leonard,

16:35.095 --> 16:36.896
you've been telling me
to settle this

16:36.963 --> 16:38.065
from the start.

16:38.098 --> 16:39.099
We are winning.

16:39.166 --> 16:40.533
Let's just keep going

16:40.600 --> 16:42.702
and get this shit done already.

16:43.803 --> 16:45.072
He's right.

16:50.977 --> 16:53.113
Is he going to die?

16:53.180 --> 16:55.182
I don't know.

16:56.816 --> 16:58.551
So what happens now?

17:00.220 --> 17:02.122
I guess we'll see tomorrow.

17:06.858 --> 17:09.662
Do you think we should
go for a mistrial?

17:09.729 --> 17:12.332
Why would we do that?

17:12.398 --> 17:14.267
No, I'm... I'm worried

17:14.334 --> 17:16.903
that the stroke is going
to make him seem

17:16.969 --> 17:19.239
human somehow to the jury.

17:22.642 --> 17:24.511
Yeah, I get that.

17:27.347 --> 17:29.216
But the odds of me
getting any of that shit

17:29.282 --> 17:31.551
into evidence at a second trial

17:31.618 --> 17:32.852
are pretty bad.

17:32.919 --> 17:34.121
Yeah.

17:41.128 --> 17:43.430
God, think about
where we started,

17:44.931 --> 17:46.233
Really.

17:47.400 --> 17:49.136
It is pretty cool.

17:52.004 --> 17:53.373
Yeah.

17:54.441 --> 17:57.043
I guess it did seem
kind of impossible

17:57.144 --> 17:59.179
to be this far, didn't it?

18:07.254 --> 18:12.158
While I'm sure we all
wish Mr. Cooperman
a quick recovery,

18:12.159 --> 18:14.827
the case must
necessarily continue,

18:14.894 --> 18:17.029
which means we must proceed

18:17.164 --> 18:20.900
without Mr. Cooperman's
testimony.

18:20.967 --> 18:22.669
Mr. Cooperman's health issue

18:22.735 --> 18:24.971
means the defense was not
given the opportunity

18:25.037 --> 18:26.539
to cross-examine him.

18:26.606 --> 18:28.908
Not giving the defense
their right

18:28.975 --> 18:30.810
to confront
the witness against them

18:30.877 --> 18:32.412
is prohibited by law,

18:32.479 --> 18:35.982
unfair, and unduly prejudicial.

18:36.048 --> 18:37.484
You are therefore instructed

18:37.550 --> 18:42.021
to disregard all
of Mr. Cooperman's testimony.

18:42.088 --> 18:43.923
It is not part
of the trial record.

18:43.990 --> 18:45.225
It is not evidence.

18:45.292 --> 18:48.195
You may not consider it
in any way.

18:48.261 --> 18:50.430
Put it out of your minds.

18:50.497 --> 18:55.202
By law it did not happen.

18:55.268 --> 18:56.803
Is that clear?

18:59.239 --> 19:01.241
Okay.

19:01.308 --> 19:03.443
Mr. McBride.

19:05.212 --> 19:06.746
Anything else?

19:08.114 --> 19:09.782
No, Your Honor.

19:10.983 --> 19:12.385
Very well.

19:13.853 --> 19:14.921
Miss Senate.

19:16.589 --> 19:19.459
Your Honor, we call
Brittany Gold to the stand.

19:48.888 --> 19:50.290
Raise your right hand.

19:50.357 --> 19:52.559
Do you, Brittany Gold,
swear to tell the truth,

19:52.625 --> 19:54.327
the whole truth,
and nothing but the truth,

19:54.394 --> 19:56.162
so help you God?

19:56.229 --> 19:59.466
You'll have to say it
for the record.

20:00.633 --> 20:01.634
Yes.

20:02.802 --> 20:03.802
Please.

