Thank you.

42:14.800 --> 42:16.010
Look, I don't know what happened

42:16.034 --> 42:18.236
on that boat that night, okay?

42:21.406 --> 42:22.808
But it wasn't a suicide.

42:22.874 --> 42:25.744
So you can tell his family that.

42:25.811 --> 42:27.612
That's not good enough.

42:27.613 --> 42:28.947
What?

42:29.014 --> 42:30.916
Of course that's good enough.

42:30.982 --> 42:32.542
What do you think,
I'm gonna sit in here

42:32.618 --> 42:34.620
and sign a goddamn confession?

42:34.653 --> 42:37.689
You just won a trial,
for Christ's sakes.

42:37.756 --> 42:38.790
Let's get...

42:38.857 --> 42:40.291
get this over with.

42:49.134 --> 42:50.636
Mr. Corey...

42:53.338 --> 42:54.673
come on.

43:03.281 --> 43:05.483
He was dumping fuel.

43:05.550 --> 43:07.318
Okay?

43:07.385 --> 43:09.855
He wasn't supposed to.

43:09.921 --> 43:11.957
Fuel for the cluster weapon.

43:12.023 --> 43:12.791
And bombs.

43:12.858 --> 43:15.794
No... There
aren't bomb...

43:17.262 --> 43:18.797
The fuel is the weapon.

43:18.864 --> 43:21.967
Okay? The fuel's what
does all the damage.

43:23.234 --> 43:24.569
You can't test it

43:24.670 --> 43:26.672
because you're not
supposed to have it.

43:27.839 --> 43:29.741
And if you're not
supposed to have it...

43:30.742 --> 43:32.343
you can't get rid of it.

43:34.079 --> 43:37.148
We got worried
there was going to be
a surprise inspection.

43:37.215 --> 43:39.718
Ryan Larson stepped up,

43:39.785 --> 43:42.153
solved the problem for us.

43:52.163 --> 43:55.466
I wonder who had
Rachel Kennedy killed.

43:55.533 --> 43:57.703
It wasn't us.

43:59.470 --> 44:00.706
We don't kill people.

44:00.772 --> 44:02.908
Oh, come on, Mr. Corey.

44:02.974 --> 44:04.375
What do you mean
you don't kill...

44:04.442 --> 44:06.353
Let me make the distinction.
We don't murder people.

44:06.377 --> 44:10.849
We kill enemies of the state.
There's a difference.

44:13.084 --> 44:15.721
We didn't kill your girlfriend.

44:20.258 --> 44:21.993
Girlfriend.

44:27.465 --> 44:30.435
Uh, we're good. Let's go.

44:47.318 --> 44:49.888
What? What happened?

44:49.955 --> 44:52.223
Well, other than some
phone troubles...

44:52.290 --> 44:53.524
What phone troubles?

44:53.591 --> 44:55.660
It's okay. We're good.

44:55.761 --> 44:56.828
We got the 50 million.

44:56.895 --> 44:58.663
- Fuck off.
- Yeah.

44:58.764 --> 45:00.631
Stop.

45:00.766 --> 45:02.567
Holy shit.

45:02.633 --> 45:04.169
- Hi.
- Hey. What's up?

45:04.235 --> 45:06.004
Did you just call me?
What do you need?

45:06.071 --> 45:07.773
Come here a minute.

45:13.411 --> 45:16.114
Uh, I'm not so good
with gadgets.

45:16.181 --> 45:18.583
I was trying to get a video,
but all I got was audio here,

45:18.649 --> 45:21.486
so I was wondering if maybe
you could help me out with it.

45:21.552 --> 45:22.888
Let me see it.

45:24.455 --> 45:25.991
The fuel is the weapon.

45:26.057 --> 45:30.061
Okay? The fuel's what
does all the damage.

45:30.128 --> 45:31.562
You can't test it

45:31.629 --> 45:34.232
because you're not
supposed to have it.

45:34.299 --> 45:36.467
And if you're not
supposed to have it...

45:37.803 --> 45:40.371
you can't get rid of it.

45:40.438 --> 45:41.940
Yeah, that's, uh,

45:42.007 --> 45:43.408
that's a serious phone issue,

45:43.474 --> 45:44.886
but I think I know
someone who can fix it.

45:44.910 --> 45:46.444
You mind if I, uh...

45:47.578 --> 45:49.014
Be my guest.

46:16.574 --> 46:18.076
- Hey.
- Hey.

46:19.945 --> 46:22.213
- Huh.
- Sorry about the case.

46:23.448 --> 46:24.715
You can't win them all,

46:24.850 --> 46:27.385
only this was a big one.

46:27.452 --> 46:30.721
Well, Donald figures
he'll be voted out,

46:30.856 --> 46:34.559
so he asked me to collect
some of his personal things.

46:37.295 --> 46:39.197
I wonder who they'll
move in here.

46:40.899 --> 46:43.401
If we'd won,
it could have been me.

46:43.468 --> 46:45.236
That was my plan anyway.

46:46.737 --> 46:48.406
I'm sure it was.

46:51.476 --> 46:53.011
You smell good.

46:55.981 --> 46:58.516
So what are you going to do now?

46:58.583 --> 47:00.886
Why? Am I fired?

47:00.919 --> 47:03.021
I'm sure you already knew that.

47:06.724 --> 47:09.060
So the partners have spoken.

47:10.896 --> 47:13.498
Here I thought
I was being so clever,

47:13.564 --> 47:16.902
helping Wendell
throw Donald to the wolves.

47:19.770 --> 47:21.572
Ç'est la vie.

47:21.639 --> 47:23.741
It should be you.

47:23.808 --> 47:25.510
It should be you in charge now.

47:27.946 --> 47:29.747
I don't want it.

47:29.814 --> 47:33.018
How very Julius Caesar of you.

47:36.221 --> 47:39.090
Is everything
a game to you, Callie?

47:40.926 --> 47:43.361
And you don't play
any games, Michelle?

47:47.298 --> 47:48.299
No.

49:24.595 --> 49:26.931
Hi. You've reached Rachel.
I'm not home right now,

49:27.032 --> 49:29.134
but leave a message,
and I'll get back to you.

49:29.200 --> 49:31.169
Thanks.
Have a great day. Bye.

49:37.408 --> 49:39.477
Hi. You've reached Rachel.
I'm not home right now,

49:39.544 --> 49:41.479
but leave a message,
and I'll get back to you.

49:41.546 --> 49:43.514
Thanks.
Have a great day. Bye.

50:22.520 --> 50:25.123
The doctor adjusted your levels.

50:26.023 --> 50:27.125
Hmm.

50:27.192 --> 50:29.060
You should feel
more comfortable soon.

50:32.097 --> 50:33.864
And your pressure's stable.

50:33.931 --> 50:35.366
Hmm.

50:39.870 --> 50:42.573
Sorry if I'm interrupting.

50:45.443 --> 50:47.345
Can you...

50:49.280 --> 50:51.549
let us have some privacy?

50:51.616 --> 50:54.819
I'd like to
talk to my old friend.

50:57.021 --> 50:58.122
Just a few minutes.

50:58.123 --> 50:59.624
Yes, ma'am.
Thank you.

51:01.959 --> 51:03.194
Hmm.

51:07.132 --> 51:08.499
Hmm.

51:17.608 --> 51:19.910
I hate to see this
happen to you.

51:19.977 --> 51:22.547
Ohh.

51:25.416 --> 51:28.386
Oh, Billy.

51:38.163 --> 51:40.498
Wow. You...

51:43.401 --> 51:45.703
You know me, don't you?

51:50.508 --> 51:53.744
Yeah. I know you.
I sure do.

51:53.811 --> 51:55.813
And that feels good.

51:58.883 --> 52:00.818
To be known.

52:07.592 --> 52:14.199
But... you think you're
the good guy, don't you?

52:17.101 --> 52:19.704
No, Donnie, I don't.

52:19.770 --> 52:22.207
Yes, you do. Ohh.

52:27.578 --> 52:31.382
You... You come down here.

52:44.295 --> 52:46.597
I do think you are the good guy.

52:50.235 --> 52:51.702
That's why...

52:55.273 --> 52:57.242
Look, I know you cannot...

52:57.275 --> 53:00.278
cannot let me suffer like this.

53:05.350 --> 53:07.585
Not even me.

53:08.453 --> 53:11.256
I'm close anyhow.

53:18.629 --> 53:19.864
Help me.

53:24.001 --> 53:25.703
It'll be easy.

53:30.174 --> 53:32.277
You don't give up, do you?

53:34.745 --> 53:37.348
You still trying
to get me put away.

53:45.122 --> 53:48.793
Yeah, I'd help you.
I'd show mercy,

53:48.859 --> 53:50.428
even to you.

53:52.697 --> 53:54.299
But you see...

53:56.401 --> 53:58.303
it's against the law.

54:04.642 --> 54:07.612
It burns you up
to think I beat you.

54:09.414 --> 54:11.416
You want to hear
something worse?

54:13.384 --> 54:15.620
I wasn't even fighting you.

54:19.457 --> 54:21.426
You know your friend
Rachel Kennedy?

54:21.492 --> 54:22.960
Don't start with me.

54:23.027 --> 54:25.730
Don't you fuck with me.

54:25.796 --> 54:28.966
She wasn't the one
we were trying to get.

54:29.033 --> 54:30.901
You were supposed to get it.

54:30.968 --> 54:32.803
She took yours.

54:32.870 --> 54:36.974
Oh, I'd kill you right now
myself if I could,

54:37.041 --> 54:40.244
and I would spit in your face.

54:48.486 --> 54:50.355
It's not going to work.

54:50.421 --> 54:52.189
It's not going to work, sir.

54:52.256 --> 54:53.624
"Sir."

55:45.410 --> 55:47.011
You know, Donnie...

55:49.514 --> 55:51.215
I really do hope it's true

55:51.281 --> 55:54.018
that your life
passes in front of you.

56:04.294 --> 56:06.431
You'll just drift away.

56:40.064 --> 56:41.699
You want some whiskey?

59:10.648 --> 59:12.216
You stinker!

